'''A-Sun Energy''', also known as '''A-SUN''', is a solar energy company that manufactures [[solar cell]]s. A-Sun sells [[monocrystalline]] and [[multicrystalline]] modules for residential, commercial and industrial applications.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.renewableenergymagazine.com/article/the-domestic-market-will-become-very |title=Interviews - Nicholas Martin, Managing Director UK of A-SUN Energy |last=Price |first=Toby |date=11 April 2011 |work=Renewable Energy Magazine |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6XkuQpqUT?url=http://www.renewableenergymagazine.com/article/the-domestic-market-will-become-very |archivedate=13 April 2015 |deadurl=no |df= }}</ref> In 2011, A-Sun provided the modules for the largest installation in the [[United Kingdom]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.solarpowerportal.co.uk/case_studies/a-sun_supplies_1.16mw_installation_in_somerset5478/ |title=A-SUN supplies 1.16MW installation in Somerset |date=24 February 2011 |work=Solar Power Portal |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Xkucd7e6?url=http://www.solarpowerportal.co.uk/case_studies/a-sun_supplies_1.16mw_installation_in_somerset5478/ |archivedate=13 April 2015 |deadurl=no |df= }}{{unreliable source?|date=April 2015}}{{unreliable source inline|date=May 2015}}</ref>
The company operates worldwide, with a factory based in [[China]]. The company’s headquarters are located in [[Hong Kong]]. A-SUN's products include both the raw material and the end products: photovoltaic cells, photovoltaic modules, and photovoltaic integrated systems.
