The '''Forestry Research Institute of Sweden''' ({{lang-sv|Skogsbrukets forskningsinstitut}}), or '''Skogforsk''', is a [[research institute]] headquartered in [[Uppsala]], jointly financed by the members of the [[Sweden|Swedish]] [[forestry]] industry and the [[Government of Sweden|Government]]. The institute aims to provide the industry with knowledge, products, and services, for more cost-effective and [[Sustainability|sustainable]] forestry, leading to increased competitiveness and realization of societal goals. Research efforts are primarily focused on [[tree breeding]], [[production engineering]] and [[logistics]]. Other important research areas are [[environmental protection]], [[silviculture]], forest [[bioenergy]] and utilization. The institute has budget of approximately [[Swedish krona|SEK]] 150 M, with a staff of 100 people, of which about 60 are researchers.<ref>{{cite web|title=About us|url=http://www.skogforsk.se/en/About-skogforsk/|publisher=Skogsforsk|accessdate=13 September 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Om oss|url=http://www.skogforsk.se/sv/Om-oss/|publisher=Skogsforsk|accessdate=13 September 2014|language=Swedish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=STIFT SKOGSBRUKETS FORSKNINGSINSTITUT, SKOGFORSK|url=http://www.solidinfo.se/foretag/stift-skogsbrukets-forskningsinstitut-skogforsk-EAAC|publisher=Solid Info|accessdate=13 September 2014|language=Swedish}}</ref>

